1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
🔹 Who is the Chief Minister?

The Chief Minister (CM) is:

Real executive head of the state
Head of State Council of Ministers

📌 Similar role at state level as Prime Minister at Union level.

🔵 Appointment of Chief Minister
Appointed by the Governor
Usually leader of majority party in Legislative Assembly

📌 In coalition governments, majority support is important.

🔹 State Council of Ministers

Includes:

1️⃣ Cabinet Ministers
2️⃣ Ministers of State
3️⃣ Deputy Ministers

📌 CM is the leader of the council.

🔴 Collective Responsibility

Council of Ministers is:

👉 Collectively responsible to State Legislative Assembly.

If Assembly passes no-confidence motion:

Entire ministry resigns.
🔹 Powers of Chief Minister
1️⃣ Executive Powers
Recommends ministers to Governor
Allocates portfolios
Controls state administration
2️⃣ Legislative Powers
Leader of Legislative Assembly
Advises Governor regarding Assembly sessions
3️⃣ Financial Powers
Key role in state budget and planning
4️⃣ Coordination Role

CM coordinates between:

Governor & Council of Ministers
State & Union Government
🔹 Important Facts
CM must be member of state legislature
If not, must become member within 6 months

📌 Similar to Prime Minister rule.

🔹 CM vs Governor
Feature	Governor	Chief Minister
Position	Nominal head	Real executive
Appointed by	President	Governor
Power source	Constitution	Majority support
Role	Ceremonial	Administrative
🔹 Constitutional Articles
Article	Topic
163	Council of Ministers
164	Appointment of CM
167	Duties of CM
